headline: Shares Of Energy Giant Williams Pop To Record High, Get Stock Strength Rating Upgrade
summary: Additionally, on Thursday the energy giant got an upgrade to its stock Relative Strength (RS) Rating, from 70 to 76.  Williams says on its website that its 33,000 miles of pipeline move a third of the nation's natural gas.  It says it's "transporting the energy that fuels homes, data centers, manufacturing facilities and more."

headline: Are Enbridge's Midstream Projects the Next Cash Flow Catalyst?
summary: ENB's C$30B+ secured midstream projects could drive new cash flows, supporting dividends as the company extends a 31-year streak of hikes.
